        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-01T15:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-29T16:00:00-05:00" n="1433" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1433">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Potsdam/7–3045</note>
                <head>No. 1433<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Text Submitted by the Soviet Delegation</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1433fn1">Submitted to the Protocol Subcommittee. It was
                        discussed at the Eleventh Meeting of the Foreign Ministers, August 1. See
                            <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_551">p. 551</ref>. Cf.
                            <ref target="#d1369">document No. 1369</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1945-08-01T23:59:59+03:00" notBefore="1945-07-30T00:00:00+03:00">Undated</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Draft Entry for the Protocol</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Regarding the Black Sea Straits</hi>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>The three Governments have recognized the necessity of revising the
                        Straits Convention, concluded at Montreux,<note n="2" xml:id="d1433fn2">Signed July 20, 1936. The substantive provisions are printed in
                                <persName corresp="#p_CMGHA1">Howard</persName>, <hi rend="italic">The Problem of the Turkish Straits</hi>, p. 25. For full text, see
                            League of Nations Treaty Series, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">clxxiii</hi>,
                            p. 213.</note> as not conforming to present conditions.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>The three Governments will continue conversations with Turkey on this
                        question.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
